1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,280
Two controllers, one runs on every node, one runs once and stops.

2
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:12,800
The demon set ensures every node in your cluster runs a copy of a pod.

3
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:16,960
Add a node, a pod appears, remove a node, it's gone.

4
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:23,800
Log shippers, monitoring agents, network plugins, cube proxy, infrastructure that has to live

5
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:24,800
everywhere.

6
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,880
That's a demon set.

7
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:32,800
A job creates pods and runs until a specified number completes successfully.

8
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,160
Not a service, a task with a finished line.

9
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:41,040
Batch processing, data migration, machine learning training runs.

10
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:45,720
Retries on failure, delete the job, pods are cleaned up.

11
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:49,160
Need it on a schedule, that's a cran job.

12
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:53,120
Demon set runs everywhere, job runs once.

13
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:56,080
Different tools for different shapes of work.

14
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:59,680
On the docks, Kubernetes, demon sets and jobs.

